cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.CE, cs.SY, cs.IT

This paper involves the design and deployment of a distributed computing system for a specific application, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The system also required efficient networking and communication capabilities, which aligns with the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The application itself involves complex calculations and required dependable and efficient computing capability, which could fall under the categories of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) or Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a dedicated PC farm and the EGEE Grid, which are both related to Information Theory (cs.IT).
